definition.value: Any six-carbon monosaccharide which in its linear form contains either an aldehyde group at position 1 (aldohexose) or a ketone group at position 2 (ketohexose).
A steroid acid consisting of 3beta-hydroxy-4beta-methyl-5alpha-cholest-7-ene having a carboxy group at the 4-position.
A  benzenediol comprising of a benzene core carrying two hydroxy substituents ortho to each other.
A monocarboxylic acid that is propionic acid carrying a 2,3-dihydroxyphenyl substituent at C-3; a microbial metabolite of quinoline.
